<html><head><meta charset="utf-8"/><meta content="width=device-width,initial-scale=1" name="viewport"/><title>Russell Dudek - USAA Resume</title><link href="styles.css" rel="stylesheet"/></head><body class="doc-body"><div class="doc-toolbar no-print"><a class="primary" href="docs/Russell-Dudek-USAA-Resume.pdf">Download PDF</a><a href="cover-letter.html">View Cover Letter</a><button onclick="window.print()">Print</button><a href="index.html">Candidate Vision</a></div><main class="document"><section class="paper"><div class="doc-header"><div><div class="doc-name">Russell Dudek</div><div class="doc-role">Process Excellence, Automation &amp; Operating Transformation Leader</div></div><div class="doc-contact"><img alt="USAA" class="doc-logo" src="assets/brand/usaa-logo-official.png"/><strong>Russell Dudek</strong><br/>Pittsburgh, PA · Planning relocation to Tampa/St. Petersburg<br/><a href="tel:+14122878640">412.287.8640</a> · <a href="mailto:russelldudek@gmail.com">russelldudek@gmail.com</a><br/><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/russelldudek">linkedin.com/in/russelldudek</a><br/><a href="https://russelldudek.github.io/USAA/">russelldudek.github.io/USAA/</a></div></div><div class="resume-summary"><div><div class="doc-section"><h2>Executive profile</h2><p>Operator-technologist who makes complex work visible, connects technical and business teams, and builds operating mechanisms that turn emerging technology into adopted, measurable outcomes. Brings more than eight years designing and implementing business solutions, direct people leadership, process controls, Lean/Gemba practice, workflow automation, and cross-functional operating transformation.</p></div><div class="doc-section"><h2>Role-aligned value</h2><ul><li><strong>Process excellence:</strong> Standard work, root cause, performance measures, fact-based prioritization, and process controls across high-reliability engineering, manufacturing, logistics, and service environments.</li><li><strong>Automation strategy:</strong> Opportunity framing across value, feasibility, data readiness, governance, adoption burden, reuse, and time-to-value.</li><li><strong>Leadership:</strong> Builds teams, operating cadence, coaching systems, escalation paths, and accountability mechanisms that make standards usable.</li><li><strong>Risk-conscious delivery:</strong> Connects human authority, evidence, monitoring, and fallback to the workflow rather than treating governance as a post-launch review.</li></ul></div></div><aside class="resume-sidebar"><h3>Candidate thesis</h3><p><strong>Scale the workflow and its assurance together.</strong></p><p>Automation earns scale when member/employee outcomes and ownership/control evidence improve as one system.</p><h3>Credentials</h3><p>Google AI Essentials<br/>IBM Enterprise Design Thinking Practitioner<br/>Six Sigma Certification<br/>OSHA 10</p><h3>Technical toolkit</h3><p>Agentic AI · LLM workflows · RAG · Human-in-the-loop design · Python · SQL · JavaScript · TensorFlow · Tableau · Odoo · Jira · Confluence · HubSpot · Slack</p></aside></div><div class="doc-section"><h2>Experience</h2><div class="experience"><div class="exp-head"><strong>Vape-Jet</strong><span>2025 - Present</span></div><div class="exp-title">Director of Operations</div><ul><li>Leads AI-first operating transformation across production, purchasing, quality, customer success, support, engineering issue flow, ERP/Odoo, Jira, HubSpot, Slack, telemetry, and AI-assisted workflows.</li><li>Connects factory, field, customer, and machine-fleet signals into prioritized work, earlier risk detection, cleaner handoffs, dashboards, standard work, training, and accountability.</li><li>Works in a software-enabled robotics and machine-vision environment with approximately 1,000 fielded robots informing support and operating feedback loops.</li></ul></div><div class="experience"><div class="exp-head"><strong>DudeWorth</strong><span>2017 - Present</span></div><div class="exp-title">Founder / AI and Automation Advisor</div><ul><li>Develops AI-readiness and opportunity frameworks that assess value, feasibility, data readiness, governance, adoption burden, reuse, and time-to-value.</li><li>Designs agentic workflow patterns using structured context, retrieval, AI agents, human judgment, escalation, decision records, evaluation, and governance rails.</li></ul></div></div><div class="doc-footer"><span>Independent candidate work product for USAA · github.com/russelldudek/USAA</span><span class="page-number">Resume · 1</span></div></section><section class="paper resume-compact"><div class="doc-header"><div><div class="doc-name">Russell Dudek</div><div class="doc-role">Process Excellence, Automation &amp; Operating Transformation Leader</div></div><div class="doc-contact"><img alt="USAA" class="doc-logo" src="assets/brand/usaa-logo-official.png"/><strong>Russell Dudek</strong><br/>Pittsburgh, PA · Planning relocation to Tampa/St. Petersburg<br/><a href="tel:+14122878640">412.287.8640</a> · <a href="mailto:russelldudek@gmail.com">russelldudek@gmail.com</a><br/><a href="https://www.linkedin.com/in/russelldudek">linkedin.com/in/russelldudek</a><br/><a href="https://russelldudek.github.io/USAA/">russelldudek.github.io/USAA/</a></div></div><div class="doc-section"><h2>Experience continued</h2><div class="experience"><div class="exp-head"><strong>Cardinal Building Products</strong><span>2021 - 2023</span></div><div class="exp-title">Regional Director</div><ul><li>Built the company's first remote regional operation.</li><li>Modernized distributed customer, CRM, commercial, fulfillment, logistics, digital marketing, SEO, and online-buying workflows.</li><li>Advanced AI-enhanced transportation-management and route-planning concepts.</li></ul></div><div class="experience"><div class="exp-head"><strong>ZeusVu</strong><span>2018 - 2022</span></div><div class="exp-title">Chief Pilot, Autonomous Systems and Aerial Data Operations</div><ul><li>Led regul